Below is a concise breakdown of how the pictured “two‐creature” structure is put together and which dictionary blocks (by index) are used without rotation.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
1)  ANALYSIS OF THE TARGET IMAGE
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
•  Overall Count and Layers  
   – There are 16 total pieces arranged into two “creatures.”  
   – The left creature uses 9 blocks stacked roughly three layers high.  
   – The right creature uses 7 blocks, also about three layers high.

•  Left Creature (9 blocks)
   1. Bottom layer: two blue cubes side by side (the “feet”).  
   2. A yellow rectangular block laid horizontally across the two cubes.  
   3. An orange vertical cylinder on top forming the “neck.”  
   4. One orange wedge on each side of the cylinder (the “shoulders”).  
   5. A red arch‐shaped block on top (the “head”).  
   6. Two small yellow half‐cylinders on top of the red arch (the “ears”).

•  Right Creature (7 blocks)
   1. A small yellow cube at the base.  
   2. A red arch‐shaped block stacked on top.  
   3. A green rectangular block bridging forward, on which two blue cubes sit.  
   4. Two orange wedges behind, forming the angled “tail.”

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
2)  REQUIRED BLOCKS AND QUANTITIES
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
To match color/shape/orientation exactly (no rotations allowed), use:

• #1 (Red arch) × 2  
• #2 (Blue cube) × 4  
• #3 (Small yellow cube) × 1  
• #6 (Green rectangular block) × 1  
• #8 (Yellow rectangular block) × 1  
• #9 (Orange cylinder, vertical) × 1  
• #11 (Yellow half‐cylinder) × 2  
• #13 (Orange wedge) × 1  
• #14 (Orange wedge) × 1  
• #15 (Orange wedge) × 2  

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
3)  STEP‐BY‐STEP ASSEMBLY ORDER
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Below is one logical order, building from bottom to top:

{
  Step1: Move block with index 2   (Left creature bottom, left foot)
  Step2: Move block with index 2   (Left creature bottom, right foot)
  Step3: Move block with index 8   (Yellow bridge across the two blue cubes)
  Step4: Move block with index 9   (Orange cylinder on top)
  Step5: Move block with index 13  (Orange wedge on cylinder’s left side)
  Step6: Move block with index 14  (Orange wedge on cylinder’s right side)
  Step7: Move block with index 1   (Red arch atop the cylinder)
  Step8: Move block with index 11  (Yellow half‐cylinder “ear” #1)
  Step9: Move block with index 11  (Yellow half‐cylinder “ear” #2)

  Step10: Move block with index 3  (Right creature bottom yellow cube)
  Step11: Move block with index 1  (Red arch on top of that cube)
  Step12: Move block with index 6  (Green rectangular block bridging forward)
  Step13: Move block with index 2  (Blue cube #1 on green block)
  Step14: Move block with index 2  (Blue cube #2 on green block)
  Step15: Move block with index 15 (Orange wedge tail piece #1)
  Step16: Move block with index 15 (Orange wedge tail piece #2)
}

Following the above steps and using the listed blocks (without re‐orienting them) reproduces the structure exactly.
